{
  "title": [
    "peek~"
  ],
  "description": "read/write to array",
  "origin": "cyclone",
  "categories": [
    "Arrays and Tables"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "index to read from or write to table"
        },
        {
          "type": "list <f, f, f>",
          "description": "writes <value>, <index> and <channel> to table"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "value to write to table (needs index at left inlet)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "channel number"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "value corresponding to given array index"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "symbol",
      "description": "array name",
      "default": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "channel (1-64)",
      "default": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "<0/1> - enable/disable clipping (to -1/1 range)",
      "default": ""
    }
  ],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "set <symbol>",
      "description": "set array name"
    },
    {
      "type": "clip <float>",
      "description": "- enable <1> or disable <0> clipping into -1 to 1 range"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[peek~] reads (without interpolation) and write values to an array via messages. Thus, not a proper signal object as it can't handle signals and works even when the DSP is off!"
}